dspace-development.title: Review and QA hosted Elements instances

comments.body:
Here's what it looks like now. I do think it's good to make this consistent with current behavior for the other not found error.

![Screen Shot 2022-09-28 at 10 02 39 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/845363/192843201-93ff2492-f0e4-413b-97be-01131e8174fe.png)

Is this error appearing when there's an indexing disconnect, and if someone hits the search results and this error happens it forces them out of search results?

If so, will we know when that happens now?

Good questions. The error seems to be coming from EZID link checker; https://ezid.cdlib.org/. They started on August 1, when we deployed the rails / blacklight upgrade. I don't know what previous behavior was. I don't think we do anything with these reports or have ever done anything with anything like them. There have been > 50,000 of them in the 2 or so months since they started.

If we want to be able to check on this sort of thing on demand, we could write a log message. But we may just as well put that off until it seems like we need it.
Ah, these are requests to the record pages, not the search results?
Yes. It's deployed on staging -- See, e.g. figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/notathing vs figgy-staging.princeton.edu/catalog/notathing
